# High-CPU process checks live here.
#
# Add checks with:
#   ~/.dots/no_stow/bin/monit-cpu-alerts add <name> <regex> [cpu_percent] [seconds] [cpu|total_cpu]
#
# Example:
#   ~/.dots/no_stow/bin/monit-cpu-alerts add foo 'foo' 30 60 total_cpu
#
# That creates a runtime check like:
#   check process foo matching "foo"
#     mode passive
#     if total cpu > 30% for 12 cycles then exec "__NOTIFY_SCRIPT__"
